Now communicate! Communicate up, down and across the organization. What's working? what's not working, what's the plan now? \
People are looking for direction and in the absence of direction, they're going to scatter in different directions. \
So 'act', 'adjust', and 'communicate'. And people will focus their priorities. Those priorities become clear, processes improve, and progress becomes much more evident. \
So act, adjust, and communicate. And the inevitable trial-and-error that accompanies all change will be more manageable, more motivating, and more timely.\
