Empathize; go ahead and acknowledge how they're feeling.\
Answer their questions, but don't speculate. If you \'93don't know\'94, you \'93don't know\'94.\
Be compassionate. You can show sympathy and concerns for their wellbeing, but you have to support the decision, and you have to support the \'93decision maker\'94.\
